# Mobile-First Device Consistency

- Treat mobile as the starting point for UI and UX changes, then scale up to tablet and desktop with responsive classes or component variants.
- Keep brand, navigation, copy, and core actions consistent across mobile and desktop unless the difference is intentional and user-approved.
- Prefer shared components for repeated UI across breakpoints instead of separate mobile and desktop implementations drifting apart.
- When changing layout, spacing, typography, icons, or interaction states, check the smallest supported mobile width and a laptop/desktop width before considering the change complete.
- If a view cannot be verified on every relevant device size, mention that gap in the final response.
